comments: Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in a legal position in Dort's (OKC) path and he absorbs the oncoming contact during the pick.
Aldridge (SAS) establishes himself in a legal position in Maledon's (OKC) path and he absorbs the oncoming contact during the pick.
Horford (OKC) establishes himself in a legal position in Mills' (SAS) path and he absorbs the oncoming contact during the pick.
Poeltl (SAS) legally contests Dort's (OKC) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes post position against Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) in the lane and the contact that occurs is marginal.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) places his off-arm against Murray (SAS) with slight extension as he releases, but Murray's momentum is what carries him away from the marginal contact.
During the inbound, Horford (OKC) and Mills (SAS) briefly engage in marginal contact prior to disengaging.
Poeltl (SAS) is in a screening position in Maledon's (OKC) path and Maledon loses his balance on his own as the two players engage in marginal arm contact.
Aldridge (SAS) establishes himself in a legal position in Maledon's (OKC) path and he absorbs the oncoming contact during the pick.
Mills (SAS) dribbles, gathers the ball with two hands, and then continues his dribble.
